## Visual Hierarchy & Layout

### Reading Patterns

**F-Pattern** (text-heavy pages): Users scan top horizontal, then down the left side.
- Place key info along top and left

**Z-Pattern** (minimal text pages): Eyes move top-left â†’ top-right â†’ bottom-left â†’ bottom-right.
- Place primary CTA at bottom-right

### Establishing Hierarchy

1. **Size** â€“ Larger elements draw attention first
2. **Color & Contrast** â€“ High contrast stands out
3. **Position** â€“ Top-left scanned first (LTR languages)
4. **Whitespace** â€“ Isolated elements appear more important
5. **Typography weight** â€“ Bold draws more attention

